      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80941120-jess?shelf=ooh-let-s-do-it-again">ooh-let-s-do-it-again</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3233099427" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8589747453107765415">A Merciful Death by Kendra Elliot is the first in the Mercy Kilpatrick and Truman Daly series.<br/>It&apos;s definitely off to a fun thrilling start which I hope continues 🤞<br/>Mercy (an FBI agent) returns home after 15 years of being away to investigate some murders, which also had some similarities to the big secret her , her brother and sister kept all those years ago.<br/>In the meantime she works with the local police department and meets Police Chief Truman Daly 😉<br/>It&apos;s an easy read, very pacy and never lets u</span>
  <span id="freeText8589747453107765415" style="display:none">A Merciful Death by Kendra Elliot is the first in the Mercy Kilpatrick and Truman Daly series.<br />It's definitely off to a fun thrilling start which I hope continues 🤞<br />Mercy (an FBI agent) returns home after 15 years of being away to investigate some murders, which also had some similarities to the big secret her , her brother and sister kept all those years ago.<br />In the meantime she works with the local police department and meets Police Chief Truman Daly 😉<br />It's an easy read, very pacy and never lets up for a minute.<br />I definitely recommend this 📖</span>
